long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: Running 64-bit workstation live. Opened a terminal, went to edit the current profile preferences. Just after the preferences dialog was displayed, I pressed the super key, and launched system settings. Immediately after the system settings window frame appeared, gnome-terminal crashed. I have no idea how reproducible this problem is.
